ge population, faces various complex global challenges in both security and defense. In this context, the formation of Cyber Corps and Marines at the service level by the Indonesian National Armed Forces (TNI) is a very important strategic step. Here are some reasons and implications of forming these corps. Facing Increasing Cyber Threats: In the current digital era, cyber threats are one of the biggest challenges for the country. With increasing dependence on information technology, cyber attacks can damage critical infrastructure and threaten national security. The formation of the TNI Cyber Corps aims to protect the country's information systems and communication networks from these threats. Maintaining Maritime Security: As a country with more than 17,000 islands and the second longest coastline in the world, Indonesia's maritime security is very important. The existence of Marines at the service level is expected to increase the TNI's ability to carry out maritime operations. Coordination and Rapid Response: With increasingly complex challenges, an organizational structure is needed that can respond quickly and effectively. The formation of Cyber and Marines Corps at the service level allows the TNI to operate synergistically and responsively to various threats. Human Resource Development: The formation of these corps also has a positive impact on the development of more skilled and professional human resources. International Cooperation: In facing global challenges, international cooperation is very important. The formation of Cyber and Marines Corps at the service level opens opportunities to establish cooperation with other countries." },
